body.name: BYKITCHEN Square Air Fryer Silicone Liners, 2 Pack 8.5 Inch Reusable Silicone Air Fryer Tray Fit for 4 to 6 QT, Air Fryer Accessories for Cosori, Instant Vortex Air Fryer and More(Inner Size: 7in)
deliveryMessages: FREE delivery Tuesday, February 20 on orders shipped by Amazon over $35
features: KEEP YOUR AIR FRYER CLEAN: Perfect air fryer insert for preventing any food residues or grease from sticking or flowing to your air fryer bottom, keep sides & bottom of air fryer almost spotless, and extend the life of your air fryer basket.

PRATICAL DESIGN: Our reusable air fryer silicone liners are designed with handles on both sides to make transferring the food to plate easier. And the bottom line holder allow oil drain from food to the edge of the tray when cooking, preventing the food from being soaked in oil.

FOOD GRADE MATERIAL & HIGH HEAT-RESISTANT: Made of premium food grade silicone, flexible, nonstick, waterproof, oil-proof, BPA free, 100% safe for daily use, perfect square air fryer accessories, fit for 4qt-6qt air fryer. Heat-resistance: 450℉ /230℃, microwave & oven safe.

GREAT REPLACEMENT FOR DISPOSABLE AIRFRYER PAPER LINER: Compared to air fryer disposable paper liners, these square air fryer silicone insert are reusable, washable. And resistant to higher temperature, no worry about get burned by heating element like air fryer disposable paper liners.

EASY TO CLEAN & DISHWASHER SAFE: These air fryer silicone tray liners are soft and flexible, you just need to flip it inside out and wash it with a brush with water, and dish soap will be easier to remove grease and residues. It's also dishwasher safe.
body.description: BYKITCHEN Reusable Air Fryer Silicone Liners for 4qt-6qt, Set of 2, 8.5 Inch Square Silicone Air Fryer Liners Compatible with Cosori, Instant Vortex, Nuwave, Chefman Air Fryer, Air Fryer Silicone Insert, Silicone Tray for Air Fryer BYKITCHEN Silicone Liners for Air Fryer Basket, make your life a little easier! SPECIFICATION: - Material: premium food grade silicone - Size: 8.5in*8.5in*2.3in - Color: gray FEATURE: - Made of premium food grade silicone, sturdy, flexible, durable, BPA free, 100% safe for daily use. - Bottom line holder allow oil drain from food to the edge of the tray when cooking, prevent the food from being soaked in oil. - Prevent food residues or grease from sticking or flowing to your air fryer bottom, save your cleaning time. - Reusable & washable & easy to clean, dishwasher safe, perfect replacement for square air fryer disposable paper liners. - Heat-resistant up to 450℉ /230℃, microwave & oven safe, perfect for baking various of food. - Fit for 4qt- 6qt air fryer, compatible with Chefman 5 QT, Instant Vortex 5.7Qt, Corsori 5QT/5.8Qt Notices: -Please kindly allow the little tolerance of measuring due to manual measurement. br>-Please wash these 5.8 qt silicone air fryer liners before using it for the first time.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to clean, fit perfectly, love them
reviews.reviewText: I wish I bought these when I first got our air fryer. I've been cleaning and scrubbing less, oily food still goes under the mat, but for the most part, there's less cleaning and I can hand clean with hand soap to get the oil out or throw it in the dishwasher, slightly folded and it comes out fine. There's no smell of the silicone when it's cooking. Highly recommened!

reviews.reviewText: I have the Power XL air fryer with and these make the racks so much easier to clean. The food does not stick and I use one in the bottom to catch additional food and grease. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Save your money and buy a more expensive one!
reviews.reviewText: Sadly, I guess this definitely make that old phrase "if it looks to good to be true, it is". They shipped them folded and bagged FLAT... it's a silicone mold that needs to be in the shape of a square for an airfryer. As you can see from the photos, it definitely does NOT keep its shape. I hoped that after using it a few times it might but, it doesn't. Makes it hard to use, hard to clean and almost impossible to store. So I'd say definitely spend a little more money on a better product.
